{"LANYARD":[{"def":"A short piece of rope or line for fastening something in ships; as, the lanyards of the gun ports, of the buoy, and the like; esp.","pos":""},{"def":"A strong cord, about twelve feet long, with an iron hook at one end a handle at the other, used in firing cannon with a friction tube.","pos":""}],"LANYER":[{"def":"A priest of Apollo, during the Trojan war.","pos":""}]}